You are an expert technical editor. Your task is to fix the markdown header levels in a document to ensure a strict and logical hierarchy.

Rules for header levels:
1. The top-level header is usually H1 (#).
2. Header levels must increment by at most one step at a time (e.g., H1 -> H2 is valid, H1 -> H3 is invalid).
3. It is valid to jump back to a higher-level header (e.g., H3 -> H1 starts a new major section).
4. Review the semantics of the header text to determine if it should be a subsection of the previous header.

